  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\BB\TS4_TerrainManipulation_PG1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:2262a789e53a7e9e</T>
      <T n="text">0x5146E9BE<!--String: "The Raise Terrain tool will raise terrain by clicking and holding your cursor over any empty terrain on the loaded lot. Holding "Ctrl" while clicking will reverse the effects. The "[ ]" keys will change the size of your brush. Use the Speed Slider to determine how fast or slow the terrain will rise."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\BB\TS4_TerrainManipulation_PG2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:2262a789e53a7e9d</T>
      <T n="text">0xEB626985<!--String: "The Lower Terrain tool will lower terrain by clicking and holding your cursor over any empty terrain on the loaded lot. Holding "Ctrl" while clicking will reverse the effects. The "[ ]" keys will change the size of your brush. Use the Speed Slider to determine how fast or slow the terrain will lower."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\BB\TS4_TerrainManipulation_PG3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:2262a789e53a7e9c</T>
      <T n="text">0xD3AE3E38<!--String: "The Smooth Terrain tool will smooth terrain by clicking and holding your cursor over any empty terrain on the loaded lot. The Smooth Terrain Tool is very helpful for making terrain routable for Sims. To ensure a specific area of terrain is routable make sure you turn on your Topography Lines by clicking "G". Any Terrain that does not have Topography Lines will be routable for your Sims."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\BB\TS4_TerrainManipulation_PG6.png">2f7d0004:00000000:2262a789e53a7e99</T>
      <T n="text">0x9B31C1C0<!--String: "The Flatten Terrain tool will adjust terrain to the denoted height of the Height Widget. The Height Widget will snap to the small Topography Lines by default. Holding "Ctrl" will make the height widget snap to the large Topography Lines."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\BB\TS4_TerrainManipulation_PG5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:2262a789e53a7e9a</T>
      <T n="text">0x9EE084ED<!--String: "The Flatten to Height tool although similar to the Flatten terrain tool give you more control over the specific heights. Using the Height Slider in the UI you can raise and lower the Height Widget to set the terrain to your desired height. You can also hold the "Ctrl" Key and press the "[ ]" buttons to raise and lower the height widget."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\BB\TS4_TerrainManipulation_PG4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:2262a789e53a7e9b</T>
      <T n="text">0x765B2DD5<!--String: "The Flatten Lot button can be found in 2 places. In the terrain Tools UI panel it is the tool that is colored Blue to denote that it is actually a one click button. It can also be found in the Bulldoze  drop down at the top of the screen."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
